{"title_page": "Prometheus Award", "text_new": "{{Infobox award\n| name           = Prometheus Award\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = 150px\n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| current_awards = \n| description    = The best [[science fiction]] novel promoting individual freedom published in the United States in the previous calendar year\n| presenter      = [[Libertarian Futurist Society]]\n| country        = United States\n| location       = \n| year           = 1979\n| holder         = Travis J I Corcoran (''[[Causes of Separation]]'')\n| website        = [http://lfs.org/awards.shtml lfs.org]\n}}\n{{Libertarianism in the United States sidebar}}\nThe '''Prometheus Award''' is an award for [[libertarian science fiction]] novels given annually by the Libertarian Futurist Society. [[L. Neil Smith]] established the award in 1979, but it was not awarded regularly until the newly founded Libertarian Futurist Society revived it in 1982.  The Society created a Hall of Fame Award (for classic works of libertarian science fiction, not necessarily novels) in 1983, and also presents occasional one-off Special Awards.\n\n== Multiple recipients ==\n\nSome authors have won the award for best novel more than once:\n\n===Thrice===\n* [[Cory Doctorow]]\n* [[Victor Koman]]\n* [[Ken MacLeod]]\n* [[L. Neil Smith]]\n\n===Twice===\n* [[Travis J I Corcoran]]\n* [[James P. Hogan (writer)|James P. Hogan]]\n* [[Neal Stephenson]]\n* [[Vernor Vinge]]\n* [[F. Paul Wilson]]\nA few authors have won the Prometheus Hall of Fame award more than once: \n* [[Poul Anderson]]\n* [[Robert Heinlein]]\n* [[George Orwell]]\n* [[Ayn Rand]]\n* [[F. Paul Wilson]]\n\n== Process ==\n\nBooks published in a given year are eligible (although books from the last few months of the previous year are also eligible if it is felt that they have been overlooked).\n\n# All members may nominate novels for the award.\n# Members of the Best Novel Committee read at least 10-12 of the nominated novels and vote for a slate of 5 finalists.\n# Full members (a higher price tier of membership) then vote on the finalists.\n\nStep 2 happens in the first few months of the following year.\n\nStep 3 happens in early summer of the following year.\n\nThe awards are given at the Annual [[Worldcon]].\n\n==Prometheus Award winners and finalists==\n<span style=\"margin:0px; padding-bottom:1px; font-size:90%; display:block;\"><span style=\"border:#aaa solid 1px; background-color:#B0C4DE;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;Winners</span>\n<span style=\"margin:0px; padding-bottom:1px; font-size:90%; display:block;\"><span style=\"border:#aaa solid 1px; background-color:lightgray;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;+&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;No winner selected</span>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" width=\"85%\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"margin: 1em auto 1em auto\"\n|-\n|+ List of winners and finalists for the Prometheus Award\n|-\n! width=\"7%\" scope=\"col\"|Year\n! width=\"28%\" scope=\"col\"|Author\n! width=\"35%\" scope=\"col\"|Novel\n! width=\"26%\" scope=\"col\"|Publisher\n! width=\"4%\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Ref.\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center; font-weight:normal; background:#B0C4DE;\" |{{sort|19791|[[1978 in literature|1979]]}}\n| {{sortname|F. Paul|Wilson}}* || ''{{sort|Wheels Within Wheels|[[Wheels Within Wheels (novel)|Wheels Within Wheels]]}}'' || [[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]]\n!style=\"text-align:center; background:#B0C4DE;\"| <ref name=\"Loc79\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center; font-weight:normal; background-color:transparent;\" |{{sort|19792|[[1978 in literature|1979]]}}\n| {{sortname|Poul|Anderson}} || ''{{sort|The Avatar|[[The Avatar (novel)|The Avatar]]}}'' || [[Berkley Books]]\n!style=\"text-align:center; background-color:transparent;\"| <ref name=\"Loc79\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center; font-weight:normal; background-color:transparent;\" |{{sort|19793|[[1978 in literature|1979]]}}\n| {{sortn