 ''Free Space'' (anthology)\n* 2001 \u2013 [[Poul Anderson]], Special Prometheus Award for Lifetime Achievement\n* 2005 \u2013 Mark Tier and [[Martin H. Greenberg]]: editors, ''Give Me Liberty'' and ''Visions of Liberty'' (anthologies for Baen Books)\n* 2005 \u2013 [[L. Neil Smith]] (writer) and [[Scott Bieser]] (illustrator), ''[[The Probability Broach]]: The Graphic Novel''\n* 2006 \u2013 [[Joss Whedon]] (writer-director), ''[[Serenity (2005 film)|Serenity]]''\n* 2007 \u2013 [[James McTeigue]] (director) and [[the Wachowski brothers]] (screenplay), ''[[V For Vendetta (film)|V for Vendetta]]'' (Motion Picture)\n* 2014 \u2013 [[Vernor Vinge]], Special Prometheus Award for Lifetime Achievement\n* 2014 \u2013 [[Leslie Fish]], \"Tower of Horses\" (novella) and \"The Horsetamer's Daughter\" (song).\n* 2015 \u2013 [[F. Paul Wilson]], Special Prometheus Award for Lifetime Achievement\n* 2016 \u2013 [[L. Neil Smith]], Special Prometheus Award for Lifetime Achievement\n* 2016 \u2013 [[Luna Brothers|Jonathan Luna]] and Sarah Vaughn, ''[[Alex + Ada]]''\n* 2017 \u2013 Mark Stanley, ''Freefall'' ([[webcomic]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.locusmag.com/News/2017/05/special-prometheus-award-for-freefall/|title=Locus Online News \u00bb Special Prometheus Award for Freefall|website=www.locusmag.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-31}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Libertarianism}}\n* [[Anarcho-capitalist literature]]\n* [[Libertarianism]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=\"Loc79\">{{cite web |url=http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus1979.html |title=The Locus Index to SF Awards: 1979 Prometheus Awards |work=[[Locus (magazine)|Locus]] |accessdate=2014-01-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016210325/http://locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus1979.html |archivedate=2012-10-16 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Loc82\">{{cite web |url=http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus1982.html |title=The Locus Index to SF Awards: 1982 Prometheu