eb |url=http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus2010.html |title=The Locus Index to SF Awards: 2010 Prometheus Awards |work=[[Locus (magazine)|Locus]] |accessdate=2014-02-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102205033/http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus2010.html |archivedate=2012-11-02 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Loc11\">{{cite web |url=http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus2011.html |title=The Locus Index to SF Awards: 2011 Prometheus Awards |work=[[Locus (magazine)|Locus]] |accessdate=2014-02-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520144124/http://locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus2011.html |archivedate=2013-05-20 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"LFS12\">{{cite web |url=http://www.lfs.org/releases/2012Winners.shtml |title=2012 Prometheus Best Novel Winners Announced |work=Libertarian Futurist Society |accessdate=2014-02-07}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"LFS13\">{{cite web |url=http://www.lfs.org/releases/2013Winners.shtml |title=2013 Prometheus Winners Announced |publisher=Libertarian Futurist Society |date=2012-07-20|website=www.lfs.org |accessdate=2014-02-07}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"LFS14\">{{cite web |url=http://www.lfs.org/releases/2014Winners.shtml |title=2014 PROMETHEUS BEST NOVEL WINNERS ANNOUNCED |publisher=Libertarian Futurist Society |accessdate=2014-07-13}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"LFS15\">{{cite web |url=http://lfs.org/releases/2015Winners.shtml |title=PROMETHEUS AWARD WINNER ANNOUNCED |publisher=Libertarian Futurist Society |accessdate=2015-07-12}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"LFS16\">{{cite web |url=http://www.lfs.org/releases/2016Winners.shtml |title=2016 PROMETHEUS AWARD BEST NOVEL WINNERS ANNOUNCED |publisher=Libertarian Futurist Society |accessdate=2016-07-11}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"LFS17\">{{cite web |url=http://lfs.org/releases/2017Winners.shtml |title=Sinisalo's The Core of the Sun wins Prometheus Award for Best Novel |publisher=Libertarian Futurist Society |accessdate=2017-03-27}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"LFS18\">{{cite web |url=http://lfs.org/releases/2018PrometheusFinalists.shtml |title=PROMETHEUS AWARD FINALISTS CHOSEN FOR BEST NOVEL |publisher=Libertarian Futurist Society |accessdate=2018-03-26}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"LFS19\">{{cite web |url=http://lfs.org/releases/2019Winners.shtml |title=PROMETHEUS AWARD AND CLASSIC FICTION AWARD WINNERS |publisher=Libertarian Futurist Society |accessdate=2019-07-06}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Science fiction}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.lfs.org/ Libertarian Futurist Society]\n* [http://www.lfs.org/releases.htm LFS Press Releases ]\n* [https://twitter.com/PrometheusAward Prometheus Award on Twitter]\n* [https://www.facebook.com/PrometheusAward/ Prometheus Award on Facebook]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160304031450/http://nccsweb.urban.org/communityplatform/nccs/organization/profile/id/311754389/popup/1 Libertarian Futurist Society: Organizational Profile] \u2013 [[National Center for Charitable Statistics]] ([[Urban Institute]])\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080928194349/http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus.html Locus Magazine's Index of Prometheus Award winners]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080109042426/http://www.salon.com/books/feature/1999/07/27/macleod_interview/print.html Award discussed in this Salon.com interview with 2-time Prometheus Award winner Ken MacLeod]\n\n[[Category:Prometheus Award winners| ]]\n[[Category:Prometheus Award-winning works| ]]\n[[Category:Science fiction awards]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 1979]]\n[[Category:Libertarian science fiction]]\n[[Category:Anarchist fiction]]\n[[Category:Prometheus]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox award\n| name           = Prometheus Award\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = 150px\n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| current_awards = \n| description    = The best [[science fiction]] novel promoting individual freedom published in the United States in the previous calendar year\n| presenter      = [[Libertarian Futurist Society]]\n| country        = United States\n| location       = \n| year           = 1979\n| holder         = Travis J I Corcoran (''[[Causes of Separation]]'')\n| website        = [http://lfs.org/awards.shtml lfs.org]\n}}\n{{Libertarianism in the United States sidebar}}\nThe '''Prometheus Award''' is an award for [[libertarian science fiction]] novels given annually by the Libertarian Futurist Society. [[L. Neil Smith]] established the award in 1979, but it was not awarded regularly until the newly founded Libertarian Futurist Society revived it in 1982.  The Society created a Hall of Fame Award (for classic works of libertarian science fiction, not necessarily novels) in 1983, and also presents occasional one-off Special Awards.\n\n== Multiple recipients ==\n\nSome authors have won the award for best novel more than once:\n* [[Cory Doctorow]] (three times)\n* [[Victor Koman]] (three times)\n* [[Ken MacLeod]] (three times)\n* [[L. Neil Smith]] (three times)\n* [[Travis J I Corcoran]] (twice)\n* [[James P. Hogan (writer)|James P. Hogan]] (twice)\n* [[Neal Stephenson]] (twice)\n* [[Vernor Vinge]] (twice)\n* [[F. Paul Wilson]] (twice)\n\nA few authors have won the Prometheus Hall of Fame award more than once: \n* [[Poul Anderson]]\n* [[Robert Heinlein]]\n* [[George Orwell]]\n* [[Ayn Rand]]\n* [[F. Paul Wilson]]\n\n== Process ==\n\nBooks published in a given year are eligible (although books from the last few months of the previous year are also eligible if it is felt that they have been overlooked).\n\n# All members may nominate novels for the award.\n# Members of the Best Novel Committee read at least 10-12 of the nominated novels and vote for a slate of 5 finalists.\n# Full members (a higher price tier of membership) then vote on the finalists.\n\nStep 2 happens in the first few months of the following year.\n\nStep 3 happens in early summer of the following year.\n\nThe awards are given at the Annual [[Worldcon]].\n\n==Prometheus Award winners and finalists==\n<span style=\"margin:0px; padding-bottom:1px; font-size:90%; display:block;\"><span style=\"border:#aaa solid 1px; background-color:#B0C4DE;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;Winners</span>\n<span style=\"margin:0px; padding-bottom:1px; font-size:90%; display:block;\"><span style=\"border:#aaa solid 1px; background-color:lightgray;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;+&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;No winner selected</span>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" width=\"85%\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"margin: 1em auto 1em auto\"\n|-\n|+ List of winners and finalists for the Prometheus Award\n|-\n! width=\"7%\" scope=\"col\"|Year\n! width=\"28%\" scope=\"col\"|Author\n! width=\"35%\" scope=\"col\"|Novel\n! width=\"26%\" scope=\"col\"|Publisher\n! width=\"4%\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Ref.\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center; font-weight:normal; background:#B0C4DE;\" |{{sort|19791|[[1978 in literature|1979]]}}\n| {{sortname|F. Paul|Wilson}}* || ''{{sort|Wheels Within Wheels|[[Wheels Within Wheels (novel)|Wheels Within Wheels]]}}'' || [[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]]\n!style=\"text-align:center; background:#B0C4DE;\"| <ref name=\"Loc79\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center; font-weight:normal; background-color:transparent;\" |{{sort|19792|[[1978 in literature|1979]]}}\n| {{sortname|Poul|Anderson}} || ''{{sort|The Avatar|[[The Avatar (novel)|The Avatar]]}}'' || [[Berkley Books]]\n!style=\"text-align:center; background-color:transparent;\"| <ref name=\"Loc79\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center; font-weight:normal; background-color:transparent;\" |{{sort|19793|[[1978 in literature|1979]]}}\n| {{sortname|James P.|Hogan|James P. Hogan (writer)}} || ''[[The Genesis Machine]]'' || [[Del Rey Books]]\n!style=\"text-align:center; background-color:transparent;\"| <ref name=\"Loc79\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center; font-weight:normal; background:#B0C4DE;\" |{{sort|19821|[[1980 in literature|1982]]}}\n| {{sortname|L.