Texans'' (also known as ''Lone Star Planet'')\n* 2000&nbsp; [[Hans Christian Andersen]], \"[[The Emperor's New Clothes]]\"\n* 2001&nbsp; [[Jerry Pournelle]]&nbsp;/ [[John F. Carr]] (editors), ''The Survival of Freedom''\n* 2002&nbsp; [[Patrick McGoohan]], ''[[The Prisoner]]'' (TV series)\n* 2003&nbsp; [[Robert A. Heinlein]], \"[[Requiem (short story)|Requiem]]\"\n* 2004&nbsp; [[Vernor Vinge]], \"[[The Ungoverned]]\"\n* 2005&nbsp; [[A. E. van Vogt]], ''[[The Weapon Shops of Isher]]''\n* 2006&nbsp; [[Alan Moore]] (author)&nbsp;/ [[David Lloyd (comics)|David Lloyd]] (illustrator), ''[[V for Vendetta]]'' (graphic novel)\n* {{hlist | 2007&nbsp; [[Sinclair Lewis]], ''[[It Can't Happen Here]]''&nbsp; | &nbsp;[[Vernor Vinge]], ''[[True Names]]''}}\n* 2008&nbsp; [[Anthony Burgess]], ''[[A Clockwork Orange (novel)|A Clockwork Orange]]''\n* 2009&nbsp; [[J. R. R. Tolkien]], ''[[The Lord of the Rings]]''\n* 2010&nbsp; [[Poul Anderson]], \"[[No Truce with Kings]]\"\n* 2011&nbsp; [[George Orwell]], ''[[Animal Farm]]''\n* 2012&nbsp; [[E. M. Forster]], \"[[The Machine Stops]]\"\n* 2013&nbsp; [[Neal Stephenson]], ''[[Cryptonomicon]]''\n* 2014&nbsp; [[Lois McMaster Bujold]], ''[[Falling Free]]''\n* 2015&nbsp; [[Harlan Ellison]], \"[[\"Repent, Harlequin!\" Said the Ticktockman]]\"\n* 2016&nbsp; [[Donald Kingsbury]], ''[[Courtship Rite]]''\n* 2017&nbsp; [[Robert A. Heinlein]], \"[[Coventry (short story)|Coventry]]\"\n* 2018&nbsp; [[Jack Williamson]], \"[[With Folded Hands]]\"\n* 2019&nbsp; [[Kurt Vonnegut]], \"[[Harrison Bergeron]]\"\n\n==Special Award recipients==\n* 1998 \u2013 [[Brad Linaweaver]] and [[Edward E. Kramer]]: editors, ''Free Space'' (anthology)\n* 2001 \u2013 [[Poul Anderson]], Special Prometheus Award for Lifetime Achievement\n* 2005 \u2013 Mark Tier and [[Martin H. Greenberg]]: editors, ''Give Me Liberty'' and ''Visions of Liberty'' (anthologies for Baen Books)\n* 2005 \u2013 [[L. Neil Smith]] (writer) and [[Scott Bieser]] (illustrator), ''[[The Probability Broach]]: The Graphic Novel''\n* 2006 \u2013 [[Joss Whedon]] (writer-director), ''[[Serenity (2005 film)|Serenity]]''\n* 2007 \u2013 [[James McTeigue]] (director) and [[the Wachowski brothers]] (screenplay), ''[[V For Vendetta (film)|V for Vendetta]]'' (Motion Picture)\n* 2014 \u2013 [[Vernor Vinge]], Special Prometheus Award for Lifetime Achievement\n* 2014 \u2013 [[Leslie Fish]], \"Tower of Horses\" (novella) and \"The Horsetamer's Daughter\" (song).\n* 2015 \u2013 [[F. Paul Wilson]], Special Prometheus Award for Lifetime Achievement\n* 2016 \u2013 [[L. Neil Smith]], Special Prometheus Award for Lifetime Achievement\n* 2016 \u2013 [[Luna Brothers|Jonathan Luna]] and Sarah Vaughn, ''[[Alex + Ada]]''\n* 2017 \u2013 Mark Stanley, ''Freefall'' ([[webcomic]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.locusmag.com/News/2017/05/special-prometheus-award-for-freefall/|title=Locus Online News \u00bb Special Prometheus Award for Freefall|website=www.locusmag.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-31}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Libertarianism}}\n* [[Anarcho-capitalist literature]]\n* [[Libertarianism]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=\"Loc79\">{{cite web |url=http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus1979.html |title=The Locus Index to SF Awards: 1979 Prometheus Awards |work=[[Locus (magazine)|Locus]] |accessdate=2014-01-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016210325/http://locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus1979.html |archivedate=2012-10-16 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Loc82\">{{cite web |url=http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus1982.html |title=The Locus Index to SF Awards: 1982 Prometheus Awards |work=[[Locus (magazine)|Locus]] |accessdate=2014-01-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016210401/http://locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus1982.html |archivedate=2012-10-16 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Loc83\">{{cite web |url=http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Prometheus1983.html |title=The Locus Index to SF Awards: 1983 Pro